content:
Escherichia coli is generally found in the colon and large intestine of the warm-blooded organisms. It belongs to a family of k-12 and B strain that is used in molecular biology for different experiments and also considered as a model organism. K-12 is the strain first confined from a sample of stool of the patient suffering from diphtheria. Different strains have been emerged in years due to various treatment agents. Expression profiling of wild type and SgrR mutant E. coli under aMG and 2-DG-induced strain were done. The RNA-seq analysis was done using illumina for strain grown, for 54 different conditions.
